\section{Conclusion}
\label{Section_Conclusion}


In this contribution, we developed a robust RS transmission strategy to address the rate and power design problems in MU-MISO systems with CSIT uncertainties.

This builds upon the existing RS approach used to boost the sum-DoF and sum-rate performances.

We analytically proved that properly designed RS schemes achieve superior max-min DoF performances compared to their NoRS counterparts.

Moreover, we showed that RS can be used to tackle the feasibility problem appearing in NoRS power designs.

We proposed a sub-optimal unified algorithm that solves the robust RS rate and power problems based on a conservative approximation. The superior performance of the RS algorithm compared to its NoRS counterpart was demonstrated through simulations.

In the extended version of this work, we seek to develop a non-conservative robust design that achieves the theoretically anticipated non-saturating rate performance under non-scaling CSIT uncertainties.






